# Security & DevSecOps Conventions

## Subprocess Safety
- Never use `shell=True`; use list args for subprocess
- Validate and sanitize all user-controlled paths before subprocess calls

## Secrets
- No hardcoded secrets; use env vars via pydantic-settings
- Document platform secret management (External Secrets, Vault) for production

## API Security
- Enable `REQUIRE_API_KEY=true` in production
- Apply rate limiting to scan/remediate endpoints (SlowAPI)
- Validate `target_path` and `manifest_path`; prevent path traversal

## Error Handling
- Do not expose stack traces to clients
- Log errors with request_id for traceability
- Use structured JSON logging
